'''Carta Worldwide''' is a Canadian software company that offers digital transaction processing, specializing in mobile and prepaid transactions. In addition to their Canadian headquarters, Carta has offices in London, Dubai, San Francisco and Casablanca. Carta operates internationally, providing financial technology and mobile payment software.

Carta<U+2019>s clients include [[Banco Sabadell]],<ref>Clark, Sarah. [http://www.nfcworld.com/2014/03/04/328162/banco-sabadell-picks-carta-hce-payments-trial/ "Banco Sabadell picks Carta for HCE payments trial"],  NFC World. March 4, 2014.</ref> [[Westpac]] NZ,<ref>[http://www.mobilepaymentstoday.com/news/westpac-tests-nfc-enabled-mobile-payments-using-hce-in-new-zealand/ "Westpac tests NFC-enabled mobile payments using HCE in New Zealand"], July 22, 2014.</ref> and Novum Bank.<ref>[http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/04/01/idUSnGNXwCdKT+eb+GNW20140401 "Novum Bank Selects Carta Worldwide as Processing Platform for Prepaid Card and Debit Card Portfolios"], March 31, 2014.</ref> The company also partners with [[MasterCard]]<ref>[http://finance.yahoo.com/news/repeat-dcr-strategies-inc-partners-194235276.html;_ylt=AwrBEiJU8cdTLhUAJqqTmYlQ "DCR Strategies Inc. Partners with MasterCard(R) to Launch a Consumer-Friendly Prepaid Reload Service in Canada"], Yahoo Finance, June 20, 2014.</ref> and DCR Strategies/TruCash<ref>[http://finance.yahoo.com/news/dcr-strategies-trucash-carta-worldwide-160633708.html "DCR Strategies / TruCash and Carta Worldwide Partner on Next Generation Mobile Payments"], Yahoo Finance, April 2, 2014.</ref>

Carta was the world's first processor to complete integration to MasterCard MOTAPS, enabling rapid deployment for NFC programs.<ref>[http://newsroom.mastercard.com/press-releases/carta-worldwide-completes-a-world-first-with-mastercard/ "Carta Worldwide Completes a World First with MasterCard"], MasterCard Newsroom, May 10, 2011.</ref> Their Charlottetown, PEI, data centre is the only secure third party issuer processing data host for financial services in Canada.<ref>[http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/prince-edward-island/carta-worldwide-setting-up-shop-in-charlottetown-1.2762607 "Carta Worldwide setting up shop in Charlottetown"], CBC News, September 10, 2014</ref>

==History==

Carta was founded in 2007 in Oakville, Ontario.<ref>[https://www.linkedin.com/company/carta-worldwide Carta Linkedin page], retrieved September 3, 2014.</ref> It is currently headed by CEO Brian Semkiw. Semkiw is the cofounder of Rand Worldwide which had 1500 employees and had secured revenues of approximately $500 million by the time it was privatized in 2007.<ref>[http://www.cartaworldwide.com/about/ Official Carta website], retrieved September 2, 2014.</ref> ''Profit Magazine'' named Semkiw "Entrepreneur of the Year" in 1996.<ref>[http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=652465&privcapId=109048521&previousCapId=876093&previousTitle=APOGEE%20SILVER%20LTD "Brian Semkiw P. Eng. Executive Profile"], Bloomberg Businessweek, retrieved September 3, 2014.</ref>

On September 15, 2014, Carta Worldwide closed the first tranche of a $12 million Series D [[venture round]]. Led by Toronto-based merchant bank [http://differencecapital.com/ Difference Capital] and [http://www.dcthomson.co.uk/ DC Thomson] (UK), the $7-million investment adds to the more than $50 million the company has invested in its digital transaction processing platform.<ref>Waddell, Nick. [http://www.cantechletter.com/2014/09/difference-capital-leads-first-tranche-12-million-series-d-carta-worldwide "Difference Capital leads first tranche of $12-million Series D in Carta Worldwide"], Cantech Letter, September 15, 2014</ref><ref>Dorbian, Iris. [http://www.pehub.com/2014/09/difference-capital-and-dc-thomson-back-carta "Difference Capital and DC Thomson back Carta"], Reuters PE Hub, September 16, 2014</ref>

==Awards==

In July 2014, Carta was named a finalist for Best Contactless Solution, at the Emerging Payment Awards in London, UK.<ref>[http://www.emergingpaymentsawards.com/2014-finalists/ 2014 Finalists], Emerging Payments Awards Website, retrieved September 3, 2014.</ref> In May 2014, Carta was named Best Virtual or Mobile Program <ref>[http://www.paymentsexchange.ca/awards/#4 Best Virtual or Mobile Program], Payments Exchange, May 29, 2014.</ref> and in 2013 the company was awarded Best Virtual Campaign at the Prepaid and Payments Awards in Toronto, Canada.<ref>[http://www.paymentsexchange.ca/2013/06/13/press-release-payments-exchange-announces-results-of-the-2013-px-prepaid-payments-awards/ "Payments eXchange Announces Results of the 2013 PX Prepaid & Payments Awards"], Payments Exchange, June 13, 2013.</ref>

